      <section>
        <h2 class="nhsuk-heading-m">Introduction</h2>

        <ol>
          <li>
            We (NHS England) have developed a digital service called NHS check if you need a lung scan.
            This is a digital way to access <a href="https://www.nhs.uk/tests-and-treatments/lung-cancer-screening/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NHS lung cancer screening</a>.
            This service is currently in pilot so is only available in certain areas and if your GP surgery is participating in the pilot.
          </li>
          <li>This service will not provide you with any results or information in relation to the lung cancer screening,
          you will need to complete your lung cancer screening by phone to receive a result.</li>
          <li>To find out more about who we are and our role, visit the <a href="https://transform.england.nhs.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NHS England website</a>.</li>
          <li>Contacting us: if you have any questions about the service, <a href="https://www.nhs.uk/contact-us/nhs-app-contact-us/tell-us-what-you-need-help-with" target="_blank" rel="noopener">contact us</a> by email: {% include '_email_us.jinja' %}</li>
        </ol>
      </section>
